**Report: Web Development Learning and Odoo Overview**

I started learning web development by studying **HTML and CSS** using tutorials from W3Schools. After understanding the basic structure of web pages, styling, and layouts, I built a simple website using HTML and CSS. This process took about **4 days** to complete.

After that, I learned **Bootstrap**, which helps in creating responsive and well-designed websites quickly. Learning and practicing Bootstrap took around **2.5 days**.

Next, I studied **JavaScript** to understand how to add interactivity and dynamic behavior to web pages. I practiced different JavaScript concepts for about **4 days**.

Based on the knowledge I gained from HTML, CSS, Bootstrap, and JavaScript, I completed **three tasks** related to web development. After finishing those, I continued with **Task 4 and Task 5**, which helped me further improve my practical skills.

Later, I started learning **Python** for backend development and programming concepts. After learning Python basics, I completed **Task 6**, which was an **Employee Management System project**.

I also learned the basic overview of **Odoo**, which is an open-source ERP (Enterprise Resource Planning) system used to manage business operations such as sales, inventory, accounting, and employee management in a single platform. Odoo is mainly developed using **Python, PostgreSQL, HTML, CSS, and JavaScript**, and it provides many modules that help businesses automate their processes.

Overall, this learning process helped me understand both **front-end and basic back-end development**, and also introduced me to the **Odoo ERP system** used for business management applications.
